A TRUCK driver is recovering after his vehicle collided with a hippo on the R33 road between Modimolle and Vaalwater on Tuesday evening, 7 March. The hippo died on the scene. Limpopo transport spokeswoman Tidimalo Chuene said the driver lost control of the truck and it overturned and lost its load. ALSO READ: Pasop, there's a lion on the loose! “The truck driver sustained serious injuries and was stuck in the overturned truck for hours. The driver was then transported to a nearby hospital to receive necessary medical care," said Chuene. Sign in to unlock all things good Chuene advised motorists to be careful when driving in that area. “Animals are reported to be roaming in that area, especially during the night,” she said. 